      • setNIFValues

        public static void setNIFValues​(NumericsImporter importer,
                                AbstractSharedValue sharedValue,
                                java.util.TreeMap map)
                         throws MissingNIFValueException,
                                InvalidNIFFormatException
        Sets the values read from the NIF file for a given numeric. Note that this method uses a Tree backed Map as error checking for certain column entries may depend on other (previous) column entries.
        Parameters:
        importer - the NumericsImporter that is reading in values.
        sharedValue - the shared value containing the properties to set
        map - the TreeMap of values read in from the file.
        Throws:
        MissingNIFValueException - when a required NIF value is not provided.
        InvalidNIFFormatException - when a value is invalidTre

      • confirmOverwrite

        public static boolean confirmOverwrite​(java.io.File file)
        Displays a dialog that prompts the user if the specified file should be overwritten. The dialog is only displayed when the file already exists, in which case the user's choice is returned. If the file does not already exist then true is returned.
        Parameters:
        file - the file to examine.
        Returns:
        true if the file exists and the user wants to overwrite the file or if the file does not exist, false otherwise
